          <th>Term</th>
          <th>What It Means</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Internet</strong></td>
          <td>The global network connecting billions of devices worldwide</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>World Wide Web (WWW)</strong></td>
          <td>A collection of websites accessed over the Internet using browsers</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>IP Address</strong></td>
          <td>A unique number that identifies every device on the Internet (like a postal address)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>DNS</strong></td>
          <td>Domain Name System — translates website names into IP addresses</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Packet</strong></td>
          <td>A small chunk of data sent over the Internet, like a piece of a jigsaw puzzle</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Router</strong></td>
          <td>A device that directs data packets to the correct destination</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Server</strong></td>
          <td>A powerful computer that stores data and serves it to users</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Bandwidth</strong></td>
          <td>How much data can travel through a connection per second</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
